description: Indian CEOs, including Amit Khandelwal, are optimistic about revenue prospects and planning mergers and acquisitions, mainly through IPOs. description: The Ministry of Education announced the cancellation of the UGC NET June 2024 exam due to integrity concerns, causing confusion among parents and students. The decision, clarified on X, affected candidates prepared for the NEET exam. The cancellation was prompted by I4C's information on exam integrity, reflecting criticism faced by NTA. Various political figures, including Mallikarjun Kharge and Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, criticized the government's handling of exams.
title: UGC NET exam cancelled, social media flooded with reactions from political leaders

description: Defending champions England brushed aside their struggles in the opening phase of the Twenty20 World Cup with an eight-wicket victory over the previously unbeaten West Indies in their Super Eight opener in St Lucia on Wednesday. England's bowlers restricted West Indies to 180-4 on the same pitch where the co-hosts had scored 218 against Afghanistan on Monday before opener Phil Salt led the way with 87 from 47 balls as the batters got the job done inside 18 overs.
title: T20 WC: Salt, Bairstow guide England to 8-wicket win over WI
Post-grads, MBAs among 17L in race for 17k Maha police constabulary jobs
Meat grinder used to destroy proof in Bangladesh MP murder in Kolkata
52°C at Mecca: 13 Keralite haj pilgrims among 922 dead

description: Former US House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, part of a high-level congressional delegation, met with the Dalai Lama in Dharamshala. Pelosi highlighted the recent US Congress legislation on Tibet, emphasizing clarity on the issue of freedom for Tibet.
title: Nancy Pelosi bats for Free Tibet in Dharamshala

description: Skeletons identified as Mithlesh and Neeraj Jatav from Ambah town were found inside a car pulled from Kwari River in Morena, MP. The couple had eloped four and a half months ago.
title: Madhya Pradesh: Skeletons found in car identified as missing ‘lovers’
Heatwave in India: Over 100 killed this summer

description: A bipartisan group of seven American lawmakers visited Dharamshala in Himachal Pradesh, India, on Wednesday, meeting with the exiled Tibetan spiritual leader, the Dalai Lama. This visit has caused displeasure in China. The lawmakers travelled to India specifically to engage with the Nobel peace laureate Tenzin Gyatso, who is the 14th Dalai Lama.
title: Why US lawmakers meeting with Dalai Lama has miffed China

description: Nine individuals, including three Indians, have been arrested in connection with the tragic fire in the Ahmadi Governorate of Kuwait, which resulted in the deaths of 50 people, including 46 Indians. Among those arrested were four Egyptians and one Kuwaiti national. The charges leveled against the defendants include manslaughter and negligence, as mentioned in the report.
title: Kuwait fire that killed 50: 3 Indians, among 9 arrested

description: 110-year-old Jiviben Patel from Vasna Chaudhary village in Gandhinagar’s taluka underwent a successful hip replacement surgery after a fall at home, defying her age.
title: Gujarat: 110-year-old back on her feet after hip replacement

description: Nagpur police commissioner suspended and shifted Wathoda police station inspector Vijay Dighe for a 48-hour delay in sending blood samples of hit-and-run case accused. The incident near Dighori toll naka resulted in two deaths and 15 injuries to the Bagadiya family members.
title: Nagpur hit-&-run: Cop benched for 48-hr delay in sending blood samples for test

description: Riaz, a former Pakistan pacer, was in November last year appointed the head of the selection committee by the Pakistan Cricket Board. Incidentally, it coincided with the comeback of veteran pacer Mohammad Amir to the national squad.
title: Watch: Virender Sehwag exposes bias in Pakistan cricket

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Wasim Akram praised India's Rishabh Pant's remarkable comeback after a severe accident, calling it an inspiring tale. Akram referred to Pant as a'miracle child' and expressed relief upon his recovery. He also praised his batting prowess and expressed collective concern in Pakistan over Pant's condition after the accident.
title: 'Woh miracle bachcha hai': Akram on Pant's comeback after accident
Louisiana classrooms to display ten commandments under new law

description: In June, Delhi faced a severe heatwave with temperatures soaring above 45 degrees Celsius, leading to frequent blackouts and overwhelming hospitals with cases of heatstroke.
title: Delhi heatwave: How to beat the heat and stay safe

description: The recovery of actor Darshan's footwear from his wife Vijayalakshmi's flat has added a new dimension to the investigation into the Renukaswamy murder case. Darshan, along with his aides, allegedly used the loafers in the fatal incident on June 8. After disposing of Renukaswamy's body, Darshan visited Vijayalakshmi before his arrest in Mysuru on June 11. Vijayalakshmi cooperated with the police, providing insights into Darshan's actions and interactions post the murder.
title: Renukaswamy murder: Cops grill Darshan's wife about his visit to her flat

description: Bigg Boss OTT Season 3, premiering on June 21, will be hosted by Bollywood veteran Anil Kapoor, succeeding Salman Khan. Kapoor shares thoughts on handling mixed opinions, addressing online trolling, and being prepared for the show.
title: Exclusive - Bigg Boss OTT 3 host Anil Kapoor on dealing with trolls

description: Water shortage in Delhi impacted surgeries at Safdarjung Hospital’s Sports Injury Centre, leading to the postponement of five scheduled surgeries. The hospital has been facing a water crisis for a month, relying on hired tankers for daily needs.
title: Delhi water crisis: Shortage affects surgeries at Safdarjung Hospital

description: India Meteorological Department forecasts light to moderate rain and winds in various parts of Delhi NCR and surrounding regions, providing relief from the severe heatwave and sweltering temperatures.
title: Relief for Delhi NCR: IMD predicts light to moderate rain today amidst intense heatwave

description: Seventeen men died in Tamil Nadu after consuming illicit arrack near Kallakurichi. More than 70 others are hospitalized in Kallakurichi, Villupuram, Salem, and Puducherry with symptoms like giddiness, vomiting, and stomach pain.
title: Hooch kills 29 in TN; more than 70 under treatment

description: India faces Afghanistan in the crucial T20 World Cup match. Rohit Sharma's team, unbeaten against Afghanistan, aims for victory in challenging Caribbean conditions.
title: India vs Afghanistan: Tactical strategies, key battles

description: Nvidia surged to the top of the global tech market, surpassing Apple and Microsoft, driven by the AI wave. CEO Jensen Huang's concern about data center space impacting sales was discussed in meetings.
title: CEO of world's most-valuable company, Nvidia, is worried about...

description: Microsoft's annual 'Employee Signals' poll showed a drop in employee satisfaction this year, with only 62% feeling they get a good deal at Microsoft. Business Insider reported that this sentiment is crucial for shaping initiatives and compensation packages at the company.
title: Why this Microsoft annual poll question is ‘important’ for company & employees

description: The Indian team, led by captain Rohit Sharma, is in a happy space and ready to play against Afghanistan in the T20 World Cup. Despite the team's confidence, they are not taking Afghanistan lightly, considering their warrior spirit and quality players like Rashid Khan.
title: Confident India eye winning Super 8 start against plucky Afghanistan

description: India's coach Rahul Dravid warned his team not to underestimate Afghanistan in their T20 World Cup match, acknowledging Afghanistan's dangerous team and impressive performances in the tournament. Dravid is well aware of the struggle his team faces at the Kensington Oval, since India defeated Afghanistan in a T20 match in Bengaluru in January, requiring two Super Overs to win.
title: 'We know Afghanistan is a...': Dravid warns ahead of Super 8 clash

description: At least 25 people have died and over 60 individuals were hospitalised in Kallakurichi, Tamil Nadu, after consuming illicit liquor. Chief Minister MK Stalin and Governor RN Ravi express shock and condolences. MS Prasanth, the district collector of Kallakurichi, visited patients at the Government Medical College Hospital in the district. Officials fear that the death toll may rise further.
title: 25 dead, over 60 hospitalised after consuming illicit liquor in Tamil Nadu

description: Varanasi's LBS International Airport expansion includes NH-31 passing through a tunnel under the elevated runway, a first in India, costing Rs 3,000 crore.
title: NH-31 to pass under Kashi airport runway
